headline: Delta to pay $78.75 million to resolve fuel dump lawsuit
summary: (Reuters) -Delta Air Lines agreed to pay $78.75 million to resolve a class action lawsuit over a 2020 fuel dump that doused tens of thousands of properties, including homes and schools, in Los Angeles and Orange counties in California.  A proposed preliminary settlement was filed this week in Los Angeles federal court, and requires a judge's approval.  The case stemmed from a January 14, 2020 incident in which  Delta Flight 89 to Shanghai from Los Angeles, carrying 167 passengers and crew, lost thrust soon after takeoff.
